-- Russia Equity Movers: Mechel, MRSK Holding, Nomos, Raspadskaya
-- B y   K s e n i a   G a l o u c h k o
-- 2012-07-17T15:43:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-17/russia-equity-movers-mechel-nomos-bank-raspadskaya-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  gained 0.6
percent to 1,430.17 by the close in Moscow.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO  Mechel (MTLR)   rose 0.4 percent to 193.50 rubles,
paring gains of as much as 2.4 percent. Billionaire owner  Igor
Zyuzin  sold about 2 percent of  Russia ’s largest producer of coal
for steelmakers.  OAO MRSK Holding (MRKH RX) jumped 5.7 percent to 1.768
rubles, the most since June 27. Russia’s largest electricity
distribution company proposed a smaller-than-expected five-year
investment program.  Nomos Bank (NMOS LI) climbed 1.4 percent to $10.95 in
 London . The Vedomosti newspaper reported the lender may buy
Otkritie Financial Corp., creating Russia’s second-largest
private bank.  OAO Raspadskaya (RASP RX), a Russian coal producer, dropped
2.7 percent to 82.26 rubles, the first decline in three days.
UBS AG cut the company to neutral from buy, citing a decline in
coal output.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ksenia Galouchko in Moscow at 
